%pyspark

# Create our initial RDD
rdd = sc.parallelize(range(500000))

%pyspark

import math
import uuid

# Do something computationally expensive
rdd2 = rdd.repartition(10).map(lambda x: math.sqrt(x)).map(lambda x: (x, uuid.uuid4()))
print len(rdd2.collect())

%pyspark

# Making use of partitions
def partition_function(partition_index, partition):
    return [{"partition": partition_index, "count": len(list(partition))}]

rdd2 = rdd.repartition(1000).mapPartitionsWithIndex(partition_function)
rdd2.collect()

%pyspark

# Cache the RDD so it can be computed faster
rdd2.cache()
rdd2.count()
for x in rdd2.collect():
    print x

%pyspark

# Show how caching affects the debug output
rdd2.unpersist()
print rdd2.toDebugString()
rdd2.cache()
print rdd2.toDebugString()
